summary: i think v's actual revenge was her (pretend) panic after her (pretend) murder attempt lol, she wanted to recreate the moment...
question: i think v's actual revenge was her (pretend) panic after her (pretend) murder attempt lol, she wanted to recreate the moment without actually putting eve in danger. i don't think v resents the stab itself as much as she resents that it made her aware of her own mortality, so i think she wanted eve to experience the same thing there, at least for a moment, and now they're even.
answer:
Oooh yeah that’s a good point! For some reason I forgot about that….letting Eve believe she was poisoned was much more drastic than a small cut on the lip. But still tamer than anything I expected. (I mean, I never thought Eve would be in danger of actually being killed by Villanelle, but I thought she’d be a little angrier).

I agree that Villanelle doesn’t resent the stabbing itself. She said herself that she see’s it as a form of connection between them and believes it brought them closer. She strokes the scar on her stomach like it’s a hickey lol. But after all that hell Villanelle went through in the first couple of episodes because of the stab wound….Eve really is getting off easy.

summary: Before this season premiered, I wrote a fic where Villanelle stabbed Eve (non-fatally) in order to get revenge for stabbing her....
body:
Before this season premiered, I wrote a fic where Villanelle stabbed Eve (non-fatally) in order to get revenge for stabbing her. But the actual show has made her even softer than I anticipated.

Other than maybe that lipstick with the blade in it, she hasn’t done anything to seek revenge on Eve. She really is just gonna let Eve get away with nearly killing her. Can I just say….WHIPPED.

summary: I find it interesting that there are still a number of people that watch Killing Eve that still don’t understand that a major...
body: I find it interesting that there are still a number of people that watch Killing Eve that still don’t understand that a major component of the show is exploring Eve’s psyche and decent into darkness.While the execution may have not always been perfect there have been signs since 1x01 that the show was going to explore those darker aspects of Eve. Maybe some more causal viewers take the show at face value and think it’s simply a stylized agent (good guy) v killer (bad guy) show and nothing more.
